summary:
Head coach of Singapore U19 and technical skills coach for the categories U10-U18.
Fulltime coach at Singapore Sports School, the national academy for players representing Singapore. 
Until 2014 football coach for Arsenal Franchise in Japan (Ichikawa). Specialised in Japanese football.
Experience in J-league academies (Vissel Kobe and Omiya Ardija). Background as a former professional and amateur football player, having played as defensive midfielder for MVV Maastricht (Netherlands), SV Meerssen (Netherlands), Schijndel SBA/Euro (Netherlands), Baronie (Netherlands) and Song Lam Nghe An (Vietnam). Also represented the Netherlands when playing for the Dutch National Student Team at Universiade in Sicily (Italy) in 1997.

Specialties: AFC-FIFA A licensed football coach.
UEFA B and UEFA C licensed football coach.
